Zest and halve the @lime{1} and cut into wedges. Trim the @spring onions{2} then slice thinly. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Quarter the @premium tomato mix{125%g}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add half the spring onion, half the garlic, the @Cajun spice mix{1%tsp} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

> Tip: add less Cajun spice if you don't like too much heat.

Preheat your #oven{} to 200C. Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into the saucepan with the spring onion and spice and bring to the boil. When boiling, add the @chicken stock powder{1}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Line a #baking tray{} with #foil{}, lay the @British streaky bacon{8} on it and bake until golden and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British pork mince{120%g} and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Add the remaining garlic and @chipotle paste{20%g} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @water{75%ml}, half the black beans and the @BBQ sauce{32%g}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir until well combined. Simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Once the rice is cooked, carefully fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest and half the coriander. Put the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} onto a baking tray then pop into the oven for ~{2-3%minutes} to warm through.

Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the flesh into a #bowl{} and chop into small pieces. Pop into a bowl and mix with the remaining black beans, the tomatoes, the remaining spring onion, the remaining coriander and a squeeze of lime juice. Add a drizzle of @olive oil{} then season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and set aside.

Reheat the chilli if you need to. To assemble, lay a warmed tortilla wrap in the middle of a wide piece of foil. Divide some of rice between them in a line down the middle, then divide the pork mixture and cheese between them then top each with a piece of bacon. Wrap them tightly up in the foil. Alternatively you can serve these as wraps without the foil if you prefer. Serve with any remaining rice on the side with the avocado salad alongside. Enjoy!